Quote:  I first became aware of the debilitating nature of this in the early 80s when a workmate's daughter went down with what they then called Tapanbui flu just before whe was due to leave for the UK on her OE... Unfortunately no one knows what causes this chronic fatigue. It has been called many names: Tapanui flu, myalgic encephalomyelitis and immune  dysfunction syndrome but it now seems that the medics in this country and Australia have settled on the term Chronic Fatigue Syndrome (CFS).
